&nbsp;</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n#!/usr/bin/perl\r\nuse strict;\r\n{\r\n    &#39;/hello/(\\w+)&#39; =&gt; sub {\r\n        return &quot;hello, $1!&quot;;\r\n    },\r\n};</pre>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Now you can put any one word in the URL instead of WHATEVER word.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Creating of dynamic page, that shows the weather forecast for London city http://your.site/weather</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	To do this, we kindly use the RSS from BBC.co.uk site. Please, create file</p>\r\n<pre>\r\nweather.sub</pre>\r\n<p>\r\n	in modules folder and write:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n#!/usr/bin/perl\r\nuse strict;\r\nuse XML::RSS::Parser::Lite;\r\nuse LWP::Simple;\r\n{\r\n    &#39;/weather&#39; =&gt; sub {\r\n# Taking the rss feed and parsing it\r\n        my $xml = get( &quot;http://open.live.bbc.co.uk/weather/feeds/en/2643743/3dayforecast.rss&quot; );\r\n        my $rp = new XML::RSS::Parser::Lite;\r\n        $rp-&gt;parse($xml);\r\n        my $output;\r\n# Template Toolkit loads weather.tpl template with parameters:  rp_count - the number of sections in the rss,\r\n\r\n# rp - function with input data: section number, name of the section, output data is contents of the section\r\n        $main::template-&gt;process( &#39;weather.tpl&#39;,\r\n            {\r\n                rp_count=&gt;$rp-&gt;count(),\r\n                rp=&gt;sub{ my $it = $rp-&gt;get($_[0]); $it-&gt;get($_[1]); }\r\n            }, \\$output );\r\n        return $output;\r\n    },\r\n};</pre>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Please, create file</p>\r\n<pre>\r\nweather.tpl </pre>\r\n<p>\r\n	in templates directory with following:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n&lt;h1&gt;Weather in London&lt;/h1&gt;\r\n[% WHILE rp_count&gt;0 %]\r\n    [% rp_count = rp_count - 1 %]\r\n    &lt;b&gt;[% rp(rp_count,&#39;title&#39;) %]&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\n    [% rp(rp_count,&#39;description&#39;) %]&lt;br /&gt;\r\n    &lt;hr /&gt;\r\n[% END %]</pre>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\